(Issue:)221 2334 MS
(CD2-17-001 Illegal member functions default arguments)521 2334 MS
[38 0 0 -38 0 0]/Times-Roman MF
(Section:)221 2378 MS
(17.3.4.4 )521 2378 MS
(para 4 [)656 2378 MS
(lib.member.functions])773 2378 MS
(Status:)221 2423 MS
(Open \(US\))521 2423 MS
(Description:)221 2468 MS
(The standard library uses default arguments to member functions of template classes that are dependent on)521 2513 MS
(template arguments in a number of places, even though such defaults are not currently legal C++.  This)521 2558 MS
(clash between the language and the library is currently resolved \(17.3.4.4 paragraph 4\) by specifying that)521 2603 MS
(default arguments are to be treated as equivalent overloadings with additional functions. This is called the)521 2648 MS
("Plum Patch".)521 2693 MS
(Defaults can be removed from the library by either eliminating the default case, or providing an additional)521 2783 MS
(overload.)521 2828 MS
