(Description:)221 1224 MS
(The description of the parsing process for the locale numeric facet )521 1269 MS
(num_get<> describes a process in which)1538 1269 MS
(characters are read from an input sequence, converted to a corresponding char value, and then accumulated)521 1314 MS
(into a numeric value.)521 1359 MS
(This process is necessarily slow, because it implies a virtual function call per character.  The alternative is)521 1449 MS
(to widen the candidate digit values \(once\) to )521 1494 MS
(char_type, and then compare the input character values)1208 1494 MS
(directly.  This allows the time-consuming operations to be done once, on the first conversion, and then used)521 1539 MS
(on subsequent conversions. This does have different semantics: only the canonical digit or sign character in)521 1584 MS
(the )521 1629 MS
(codeset is recognised.)578 1629 MS
(This proposal could have a substantial effect on the performance of numeric input parsing.)521 1719 MS
(Proposed Resolution:)221 1809 MS
