(The draft makes no statement about whether or not pointers/references remain valid DURING \(not after\))521 261 MS
(vector::insert. Since the value being inserted is a reference to const object, it is unclear whether or not you)521 306 MS
(can insert an element of a vector into another location of that vector.  For example \(recalling from p. 23-5)521 351 MS
(Table 69 that )521 396 MS
(push_back is defined in terms of insert\):)734 396 MS
[38 0 0 -38 0 0]/Courier MF
(vector<int> v\(100\);)671 435 MS
