[38 0 0 -38 0 0]/Times-Roman MF
(The library implementations that I have seen do accommodate the code above because \(when capacity must)521 521 MS
(be increased\) they fill-in the new memory region completely before destroying the objects in the original)521 566 MS
(memory.  I would suggest that the committee require that references into the vector remain valid during \(but)521 611 MS
(not after\) the insertion. If such a restriction is not imposed, I would suggest that the standard explicitly say)521 656 MS
(that code like the example above is undefined.)521 701 MS
