(Issue:)221 577 MS
(CD2-27-018 Suppressing )521 577 MS
(iostreams exceptions)934 577 MS
[38 0 0 -38 0 0]/Times-Roman MF
(Section:)221 621 MS
(Annex D [)521 621 MS
(depr])680 621 MS
(Status:)221 666 MS
(Closed)521 666 MS
(Description:)221 711 MS
(The stream classes for type char shall not throw any exceptions if the exception mask is set to zero. We)521 756 MS
(think that users will expect that clearing the exception mask will suppress all exceptions from iostreams. In)521 801 MS
(other words, there is a demand for a true compatibility mode to existing implementations of the old tiny)521 846 MS
(character iostreams.)521 891 MS
(It is our understanding that in general iostreams is not required to catch all conceivable exceptions, not even)521 936 MS
(if the exception mask is set to zero. For instance, exceptions that might be thrown by an operation of the)521 981 MS
(character or the traits type need not be suppress. All that is said is that exceptions raised by the stream)521 1026 MS
(buffer will be caught by the stream classes and will result in badbit set, which then might or might not raise)521 1071 MS
(an exception, depending on the mask.)521 1116 MS
(Proposed Resolution:)221 1161 MS
(For the sake of compatibility we suggest to require the tiny character streams to exhibit truly compatible)521 1206 MS
(behavior and suppress ALL exceptions in case the exception mask is cleared.)521 1251 MS
(Requester:    )221 1341 MS
(Klaus )521 1341 MS
(Kreft & Angelika Langer <)620 1341 MS
(langer@camelot.de>)1034 1341 MS
